# Team protocol

> ⚠️ **Stub — Phase 1.**

## Ownership boundary

Don't write in another teammate's zone (defined in `ROLE_SPECS.md`).
If you need a change there, message them.

## Handoff phrases (stable across runs for grep-ability)

| From → To | Phrase | When |
|---|---|---|
| Data Eng → Feature Eng | `Providers ready for <feature>:` | After provider typedefs land |
| Feature Eng → Tester | `Controller for <feature> ready.` | After controller exports |
| Tester → Reviewer | `Tests for <feature> ready:` | After tests green |
| Reviewer → Lead | `Reviewer sign-off:` | After DoD verified |
| Anyone → Lead | `Blocked on:` | When stalled >5 minutes |

## Conflict resolution

1. Single-owner rule: the file's owner does the edit; others send patches
2. Disagreement: escalate to Lead
3. Reviewer override: responsible teammate fixes immediately

## Cadence

- Lead checks task list every ~5 min via `Ctrl+T`
- Teammates self-report blockers with `Blocked on:`
- Reviewer audits in flight (not at end)
- Final retrospective is mandatory before cleanup

## Anti-patterns

- Lead writing code during the run
- Teammates spawning sub-teams (no nesting)
- Reviewer doing the work for the violator
- Skipping the retrospective when "everything went well"
